{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "auth-password-reset-e2e",
    "name": "Auth \u2013 Password Reset (3-step: POST /password/reset \u2192 POST /password/reset/verify \u2192 PUT /password/reset)",
    "description": "E2E tests for the 3-step password reset flow.\n\nEndpoints:\n  POST /api/v1/auth/password/reset          (forgot-password: request OTP)\n  POST /api/v1/auth/password/reset/verify   (verify-reset-code: validate OTP, get grant token)\n  PUT  /api/v1/auth/password/reset          (reset-password: consume grant token, update password)\n\nFolder execution order (orchestrated by make e2e-password):\n  1. setup             \u2014 register gmail_test_email, fetch verification OTP from Gmail, verify email\n  2. happy-path        \u2014 login (capture pre-reset token) \u2192 POST /password/reset \u2192 Gmail OTP \u2192\n                         POST /password/reset/verify wrong code \u2192 422,\n                         POST /password/reset/verify correct code \u2192 200 (fpw_reset_token),\n                         PUT /password/reset (fpw_reset_token) \u2192 200,\n                         login new pw \u2192 200, login old pw \u2192 401,\n                         /me with pre-reset token \u2192 401 (blocklist),\n                         POST /password/reset/verify replay \u2192 422,\n                         PUT /password/reset with stale grant token \u2192 422\n  3. anti-enumeration  \u2014 unknown email \u2192 202, unverified email \u2192 202\n  4. validation        \u2014 all 422/413 input-error cases\n  5. rate-limiting-fpw \u2014 shared fpw:ip: bucket (burst=3): 3 warmups \u2192 4th \u2192 429\n  6. rate-limiting-rpw \u2014 shared rpw:ip: bucket (burst=5): 5 warmups \u2192 6th \u2192 429\n\nAll test users use @e2e.test emails (or gmail_test_email).\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before this collection.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Registers the gmail_test_email user, fetches the verification OTP from Gmail, and verifies the email.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup account)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) { console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set'); }",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_new_password', 'NewFpwP@ss2!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set'); return; }",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email...');",
                  "const start = Date.now(); while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err || res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No verification email found.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed'); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json(); let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) { const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html'); if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
                  "        else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) { body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_vfy_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] Verification OTP stored in fpw_vfy_code:', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"FpwHappy\", \"email\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{fpw_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verification \u2192 200 (consume verification OTP)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('fpw_vfy_code');",
                  "if (!code) { console.error('[ERROR] fpw_vfy_code is empty \u2014 Gmail fetch did not complete.'); }"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{fpw_vfy_code}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verification", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "verification"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "happy-path",
      "description": "Full 3-step password-reset scenario:\n  1.  Login \u2192 capture pre-reset access token (fpw_pre_reset_token)\n  2.  POST /password/reset \u2192 202, fetch password-reset OTP from Gmail (fpw_otp)\n  3.  POST /password/reset/verify wrong code (000000) \u2192 422\n  4.  POST /password/reset/verify correct fpw_otp \u2192 200 (capture fpw_reset_token)\n  5.  PUT /password/reset (fpw_reset_token + fpw_new_password) \u2192 200\n  6.  POST /login with fpw_new_password \u2192 200\n  7.  POST /login with fpw_password (old) \u2192 401\n  8.  GET /me with fpw_pre_reset_token \u2192 401 (blocklist)\n  9.  POST /password/reset/verify with fpw_otp (consumed) \u2192 422\n  10. PUT /password/reset with stale fpw_reset_token \u2192 422",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /login \u2192 200 (capture pre-reset access token)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));", "const body = pm.response.json();", "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);", "pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_pre_reset_token', body.access_token);"] } }],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{fpw_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /password/reset \u2192 202 (forgot-password: issue OTP, fetch from Gmail)",
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "type": "text/javascript",
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('status is 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                "pm.test('body has correct anti-enumeration message', () => { pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.eql('if that email is registered and verified, a password reset code has been sent'); });",
                "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set'); return; }",
                "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for password-reset email...');",
                "const start = Date.now(); while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Reset your\" newer_than:1h');",
                "pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err, res) => {",
                "    if (err || res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail failed'); return; }",
                "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No reset email found.'); return; }",
                "    pm.sendRequest({ url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full', method: 'GET', header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token } }, (err2, res2) => {",
                "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed'); return; }",
                "        const msg = res2.json(); let body = '';",
                "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                "        if (parts && parts.length) { const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html'); if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
                "        else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) { body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/')); }",
                "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found.'); return; }",
                "        pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_otp', match[1]);",
                "        console.log('[INFO] Password-reset OTP stored in fpw_otp:', match[1]);",
                "    });",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_email}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /password/reset/verify \u2192 422 (wrong code \u2014 ErrInvalidCode, attempt counter = 1)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const otp = pm.collectionVariables.get('fpw_otp');",
                  "if (!otp) { console.error('[ERROR] fpw_otp is empty \u2014 Gmail fetch did not complete.'); }"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));",
                  "pm.test('code is validation_error', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"code\": \"000000\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset/verify", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset", "verify"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /password/reset/verify \u2192 200 (correct fpw_otp \u2014 capture fpw_reset_token)",
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "type": "text/javascript",
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "const body = pm.response.json();",
                "pm.test('reset_token present', () => pm.expect(body.reset_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                "pm.collectionVariables.set('fpw_reset_token', body.reset_token);",
                "console.log('[INFO] Grant token saved as fpw_reset_token:', body.reset_token);"
              ]
            }
          }],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{fpw_otp}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset/verify", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset", "verify"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT /password/reset \u2192 200 (reset-password: fpw_reset_token + fpw_new_password)",
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "type": "text/javascript",
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('message is \"password reset successfully\"', () => { pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.eql('password reset successfully'); });"
              ]
            }
          }],
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"reset_token\": \"{{fpw_reset_token}}\", \"new_password\": \"{{fpw_new_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login with NEW password \u2192 200",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));", "pm.test('access_token present', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);"] } }],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{fpw_new_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /login with OLD password \u2192 401",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));", "pm.test('code is invalid_credentials', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('invalid_credentials'));"] } }],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{fpw_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /me with PRE-RESET access token \u2192 401 (blocklist active via KV store)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 401 (pre-reset token blocklisted)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"] } }],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{fpw_pre_reset_token}}" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/profile/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "profile", "me"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /password/reset/verify \u2192 422 (OTP now consumed \u2014 ErrTokenNotFound)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));", "pm.test('code is validation_error (ErrTokenNotFound)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"] } }],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{fpw_otp}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset/verify", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset", "verify"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT /password/reset \u2192 422 (stale grant token \u2014 deleted after first use)",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));", "pm.test('code is validation_error (stale grant)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"] } }],
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"reset_token\": \"{{fpw_reset_token}}\", \"new_password\": \"{{fpw_new_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "anti-enumeration",
      "description": "POST /password/reset: every path returns 202 + identical body.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[POST /password/reset] unknown email \u2192 202 (anti-enumeration)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": ["pm.variables.set('fpw_ghost_email', 'fpw-ghost-' + Date.now() + '@e2e.test');"]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "pm.test('body is the correct anti-enumeration message', () => { pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.eql('if that email is registered and verified, a password reset code has been sent'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_ghost_email}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "[POST /password/reset] email exists but account is unverified \u2192 202 (anti-enumeration)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = 'fpw-unvfy-' + Date.now() + '@e2e.test';",
                  "pm.variables.set('fpw_unvfy_email', email);",
                  "const baseUrl = pm.environment.get('base_url');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({ url: baseUrl + '/api/v1/auth/register', method: 'POST', header: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, body: { mode: 'raw', raw: JSON.stringify({ display_name: 'FpwUnvfy', email: email, password: 'P@ssw0rd1!' }) } }, (err, res) => { if (err || res.code !== 201) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not register fpw-unvfy account:', err || res.code); } });"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "pm.test('body is the correct anti-enumeration message', () => { pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.eql('if that email is registered and verified, a password reset code has been sent'); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{fpw_unvfy_email}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/password/reset", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "password", "reset"] }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "validation",
      "description": "All input-validation cases for POST /password/reset, POST /password/reset/verify, and PUT /password/reset.",
      "item": [
